    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="711" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 1, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received Jan. 17.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 751.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that a
                            telegram, just received from Consul Jewett at Sivas, informs me that he
                            has left Sivas for Marsovan.</p>
                <p>The apprehension of a renewed massacre which prevented him several days
                            ago from going under my telegraphic order to Marsovan, temporarily, on
                            the application of missionaries here, no longer exists, I presume, at
                            Sivas.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
